  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Environmental Degradation, Climate Change and Migration: Global Review and Summary of Research and Forecasts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project provides a reliable evidence base information on the extent of environmental degradation and the effects of climate change affecting the decision to migrate. The project will produce a final report including a review and assessment of research, forecasts and proposed responses to environmental and climate related migration flows. Key to the development of the final report is feedback given at an expert workshop and international conference. Adelphi, a non-profit think tank for applied environmental research and policy analysis based in Berlin, will be the lead agency in carrying out the project. Adelphi will organize the workshop, conference and various coordination meetings, while IOM will be the implementing partner tasked with writing the research report.</narrative>
  </description>
